  "body": "### Description\r\nTracking issue for work required to fully support Kiln meta-spec (https://hackmd.io/@n0ble/kiln-spec)\r\n\r\n*M0* (Implementation started):\r\n * [x] Create tracking issue (this one!)\r\n\r\n*M1* (Kiln v1 Spec implemented):\r\n * [x] Support [Consensus spec v1.1.9](https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/tree/v1.1.9/specs/bellatrix)\r\n * [x] Pass Consensus spec v1.1.9 reference tests\r\n * [x] Rename \"Merge\" -> \"Bellatrix\" \r\n * [x] Rename `execute_payload` to `notify_new_payload`\r\n * [x] Rename `receipt_root` -> `receipts_root`\r\n * ~[ ] Run against `mergemock`~ - merge mock doesn't support the `eth` namespace as required by Engine API so merge block can't be created.\r\n * [x] #5057\r\n\r\n*M2* (Kiln v2 Spec implemented):\r\n * [x] #4958 Support authentication for engine API\r\n * [x] #4956 Use engine_exchangeTransitionConfigurationV1 to check EL config\r\n * [x] #5045\r\n\r\n*M3* (Many-toMany Interop):\r\n * [x] Run many:many devnet with transition (`TTD` occurring 8+ epochs in the beacon chain)\r\n * [x] Send EL Txs that transfer ETH and deploy a contract which are successfully executed on chian\r\n\r\n*M4* (Weekly devnet):\r\n * [x] Participate in EF led weekly devnet\r\n * [x] Be on the devnet during the merge transition process and process EL TXs\r\n * [x] Sync from genesis using Optimistic Sync\r\n\r\n*M5* (All-to-All persistent testnet):\r\n * [ ] Kiln specification considered feature complete for mainnet Merge\r\n * [x] Run many:many devnet with transition\r\n * [x] Run stable on devnet\r\n * [x] Create README for the public to connect (https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/latest/Tutorials/Merge-Testnet/)\r\n\r\n*M6* (Kiln code released)\r\n * [x] Mainnet-compatibile sync support\r\n * [x] Merge Kiln code into main branch\r\n * [x] Add `--network kiln` CLI flag\r\n * [x] Add basic documentation for public to connect to Kiln\r\n * [x] Stable release with Kiln support",
